  "status": "Refused",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The application has failed to demonstrate through the provision of sufficient evidence that the subject site has been vacant for a continuous period of at least 3 months immediately prior to the date of the application for prior approval. Therefore, the proposed development fails to comply with Condition MA.1(a) of Part 3, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended).",
    "Reason : 2 - The application has failed to demonstrate adequate ceiling height required to provide residential accommodation in line with Paragraphs 9(A) and 9(B) of Article 3 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) Order 2015 (as amended).",
    "Reason : 3 - The local planning authority is not satisfied that the proposed external alterations fall within any part of Class MA of Part 3, Schedule 2 of the Town and Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 (as amended)."
